added.title: The Grid Car
added.description: Tulip, a headstrong 13-year-old girl, finds a mysterious train where every car contains its own universe.

added.title: The Beach Car
added.description: Tulip strikes a deal with a cat in an attempt to get home, but is the price worth it?

added.title: The Corgi Car
added.description: Tulip and One-One explore a car full of Corgis and face off against a mysterious monster.

added.title: The Crystal Car
added.description: Tulip, Atticus, and One-One enter a crystal forest car and have to take part in a musical ritual.

added.title: The Cat's Car
added.description: Tulip has to face her past.

added.title: The Mall
added.description: The Bears go the mall and encounter their human counterparts.

added.title: Cosmic Bupkiss
added.description: A storm blocks Oscar and Hedgehog's one chance to see a comet.

added.title: Radio Silence
added.description: Oscar must get Hedgehog a special sandwich in order to save their friendship.

added.title: Director's Cut
added.description: Oscar receives a camcorder from his parents and sets out to prove to them the magic on the island is real.

added.title: Haunted Campfire
added.description: The campers must battle ghosts of their own creation after their scary stories mysteriously come true.

added.title: The Attack
added.description: The Ninja celebrate their escape from the Vermillion Army and their retrieval of the Emerald Time Blade but with Acronix and Krux determined to get their Blade back, the Airjitzu Temple becomes a battleground.

added.title: Secrets Discovered
added.description: Secrets are revealed as Nya confronts the Samurai X imposter, Kai pursues the truth about his parents and the other Ninja desperately seek to locate and rescue Master Wu. But as usual, some answers only lead to more questions.

added.title: Pause and Effect
added.description: Kai confronts his dad for aiding the Hands of Time only to discover his parents are actually Acronix and Krux's captives. Meanwhile, as the Ninja work to free Wu, Cyrus Borg and the rest of the Hands of Time's captives, a third Time Blade arrives, one with the power to temporarily stop time!

added.title: Out of the Fire and into the Boiling Sea
added.description: The Hands of Time blackmail Kai and Nya into using their combined elemental powers to retrieve the fourth and final Time Blade from the Boiling Sea with the promise the siblings can use its reversal power to save the quickly-fading Master Wu. Meanwhile, the Ninja and Cyrus Borg get unexpected help from Samurai X as they attempt to destroy the Hands of Time's time-travelling snake mech before it's operational.

added.title: Lost in Time
added.description: Kai and Nya stow away aboard Krux and Acronix's time traveling snake mech in a desperate attempt to save Master Wu. But when they arrive in the past, they must help the Elemental Masters prevent the Hands of Time from literally re-writing NinjaGo history. Meanwhile, the the Ninja remain in the rapidly-shifting present trying to help Kai and Nya's father, who was hit with a Time Punch.

added.title: Parley Part 1
added.description: Megatron and Optimus parley in an attempt to unite against Starscream.

added.title: Parley Part 2
added.description: The Autobot-Decepticon peace talks breaks down after Slipstream returns with a dire warning.

added.title: Starscream's Children Part 1
added.description: The Autobots received a distress call from the Nemesis and must come to the aid of their arch-enemies.

added.title: Starscream's Children Part 2
added.description: Starscream reveals his scraplet army, incapacitating the Autobots and Decepticons and setting up a show down between him and Cheetor.

added.title: Spotted Part 1
added.description: Worried about finding a useful position among the Autobots, Cheetor learns how to become an Autobot Scout from Bumblebee.

added.title: Spotted Part 2
added.description: Cheetor's scout training with Bee lands them in the clutches of Starscream who tests an evil experiment on them.

added.title: Origin of Species
added.description: Origin of Species, Part 1: Dan meets his partner Bakugan Drago for the first time and we learn about the incident that happened on Earth twelve years ago./Origin of Species, Part 2: Dan and friends win the Bakugan Battle, firmly establishing the Awesome Ones as our heroes and Bakugan Brawlers.

added.title: Burger Run/Monkey See, Monkey Don't
added.description: Burger Run: When the local Burger Joint is being threatened by a rogue Bakugan, Dan steps up to save the day and the burgers!/Monkey See, Monkey Don't: The AO stop neighborhood kids from copycat behavior (namely, using their Bakugan for frivolous reasons).

added.title: Bully for You/Trolling for Laughs
added.description: Bully for You: The AO must handle a neighborhood bully who is using his Bakugan to pick on the local kids./Trolling for Laughs: Wynton's constant practical jokes wear thin on his Bakugan Trox so the Bakugan decide to teach him a lesson.

added.title: Flower Power
added.description: Mega Man must battle Wood Man for the fate of the Corpse Flower, a rare and noxious bloom that's stinking up all of Silicon City.

added.title: Enemy of My Enemy
added.description: When a grudge match between Fire Man and Namagem threatens to level Silicon City, Mega Man must intervene and ultimately choose a side to prevent collateral damage.

added.title: Old School
added.description: Mega Man must stop Chaotique from making Silicon Central disappear, as in literally erasing the school at a subatomic level, while learning life lessons from a rambling old-bot named Hal.

added.title: This Is Not a Drill
added.description: Mega Man and Dr. Light must set aside a father-son disagreement to stop Drill Man from taking revenge on his own overbearing father.

added.title: A Man Man for All Seasons
added.description: When a run-in with the Hoover Gang leaves Aki unable to transform into Mega Man, he must don a cheap costume and enlist the unlikeliest of sidekicks, Man Man!
